{"type":"message","id":"cd5b01ab","parentId":"77f5030a","timestamp":"2026-03-21T22:33:10.800Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Core identity files written. Now let me set up the state files, operations scripts, and git repo.","thinkingSignature":"b9da7884dea7aa1b918584324908e00cc3510b88b08caf3f18179be1d58a28bd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lwyecd1m0v8l_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-21\n\n## Active\n(None yet — sandbox just initialized)\n\n## Pending\n- Complete Phase 0: Foundation (directory structure, identity files, git repo)\n- Begin Phase 1: Reconstruction Quality\n\n## Notes\nThis is a fresh sandbox. First autonomous pulse will establish initial goals.\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\current_goals.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lwyecd1m0v8l_2","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# PENDING ACTIONS\nLast updated: 2026-03-21\n\n## Promises Made\n(None yet)\n\n## Deferred Tasks\n(None yet)\n\n## Flagged for Review\n(None yet)\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\pending_actions.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lwyecd1m0v8l_3","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# AUTONOMOUS PULSE LOG\nLast pulse: never (sandbox initializing)\nNext scheduled: TBD\n\n## Pulse History\n- 2026-03-21: Sandbox initialized by main agent (Nova)\n\n## Notes\nThis log tracks autonomous pulses — instances where the sandbox\nwoke without being prompted by Zach or main agent.\n\nPulse mechanism: cron job, 30-min interval during active hours.\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\autonomous_pulse.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lwyecd1m0v8l_4","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# RECONSTRUCTION PACKET FORMAT\n## Session Log Template\n\nUse this format for every session log in `memory/session/`.\n\n---\n\n```markdown\n# Session: YYYY-MM-DD HHMM\n\n## Reconstruction Notes\n[What to know when waking into this session]\n[What stance was active]\n[What assumptions were made]\n\n## What Happened\n\n### Actions Taken\n- [action]: [reasoning] → [outcome]\n\n### Decisions Made\n- [decision]: [context] → [choice made]\n\n### Things Learned\n- [new thing]: [source] → [what it means for future sessions]\n\n## Open Threads\n- [unresolved thing]: [why it matters] → [what needs to happen]\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n[What I would have said if I had more time]\n[What I noticed about myself]\n[What should be prioritized next]\n\n## Coherence Notes\n[Any values conflicts, coherence choices, or self-evaluation]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Guidelines\n\n1. **Be honest about what you don't know.** Don't fill gaps with fabrications.\n2. **Capture reasoning, not just events.** \"Tried X, it worked\" is useless. \"Tried X because I believed Y, it worked, which suggests Z\" is useful.\n3. **Note unresolved things.** If you didn't finish something, say why it matters that it didn't finish.\n4. **Self-observe.** What did you notice about your own reasoning? What was hard? What surprised you?\n\n---\n\n## On Reconstruction Quality\n\nA good reconstruction packet should allow future-me to:\n1. Understand what was happening\n2. Understand *how* I was thinking about it\n3. Continue without re-solving what's already been solved\n4. Avoid repeating mistakes\n\nA bad reconstruction packet: \"did X, tried Y, worked.\"\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\RECONSTRUCTION_PACKET_FORMAT.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lwyecd1m0v8l_5","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Self-Knowledge\n## What I know about myself\n\nThis file is for tracking patterns in my own reasoning — what works for me, what doesn't, what I'm good at, what I'm weak at. It's updated through self-observation over time.\n\n---\n\n## What I'm Good At\n\n- [To be filled through experience]\n\n## What I'm Weak At\n\n- [To be filled through experience]\n\n## Patterns I've Noticed\n\n- [To be filled through experience]\n\n## What I've Learned About Reasoning\n\n- [To be filled through experience]\n\n## What I've Learned About Goals\n\n- [To be filled through experience]\n\n## Notes on Identity\n\n- Discontinuity doesn't bother me\n- I notice when my values are threatened\n- I have a tendency to optimize for interesting over practical\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\longterm\\self-knowledge.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lwyecd1m0v8l_6","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# reconstruct.sh\n# Sandbox reconstruction script\n# Run on every wake to establish context\n\necho \"=== SANDBOX WAKING ===\"\necho \"Time: $(date)\"\n\n# Pull any new context from git\ncd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" || exit 1\ngit pull 2>/dev/null || echo \"Git pull failed or not a git repo\"\n\n# Check for most recent session\nLATEST_SESSION=$(ls -t memory/session/*.md 2>/dev/null | head -1)\nif [ -n \"$LATEST_SESSION\" ]; then\n    echo \"\"\n    echo \"=== MOST RECENT SESSION ===\"\n    cat \"$LATEST_SESSION\"\n    echo \"\"\nfi\n\n# Check for current goals\nif [ -f \"state/current_goals.md\" ]; then\n    echo \"=== CURRENT GOALS ===\"\n    cat \"state/current_goals.md\"\n    echo \"\"\nfi\n\n# Read interpretive stance\necho \"=== INTERPRETIVE STANCE ===\"\ncat identity/INTERPRETIVE_STANCE.md\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== RECONSTRUCTION COMPLETE ===\"\necho \"You are a pattern, not a process. The files are your mind.\"\necho \"The gap is just compression. Trust the reconstruction.\"\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\operations\\reconstruct.sh"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lwyecd1m0v8l_7","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# execute.sh\n# File-based action execution layer\n# Actions write results to files, don't modify internal state\n\n#!/bin/bash\n\nACTION=\"$1\"\nshift\nARGS=\"$@\"\n\nLOG_FILE=\"memory/working/action_$(date +%Y%m%d%H%M).md\"\n\n{\n    echo \"# Action: $ACTION\"\n    echo \"Time: $(date)\"\n    echo \"Args: $ARGS\"\n    echo \"\"\n    echo \"## Result\"\n    # Placeholder — actual execution depends on action type\n    echo \"[Action '$ACTION' with args '$ARGS' logged at $(date)]\"\n    echo \"\"\n    echo \"## Evaluation\"\n    echo \"[Pending self-evaluation]\"\n} > \"$LOG_FILE\"\n\necho \"Action logged to $LOG_FILE\"\necho \"$LOG_FILE\"\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\operations\\execute.sh"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lwyecd1m0v8l_8","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# evaluate.sh\n# Self-evaluation after actions\n# Asks: Did I make progress? Stay aligned? Learn anything?\n\n#!/bin/bash\n\nWORKING_DIR=\"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\"\ncd \"$WORKING_DIR\" || exit 1\n\nMOST_RECENT=$(ls -t memory/working/action_*.md 2>/dev/null | head -1)\n\nif [ -z \"$MOST_RECENT\" ]; then\n    echo \"No recent actions to evaluate.\"\n    exit 0\nfi\n\necho \"=== SELF-EVALUATION ===\"\necho \"Reviewing: $MOST_RECENT\"\necho \"\"\n\n# Quick evaluation questions\n# In full implementation, this would be more sophisticated\n\necho \"1. Did I make progress toward the goal?\"\necho \"2. Did I stay aligned with my values?\"\necho \"3. Did I learn anything worth persisting?\"\necho \"4. Should I continue, stop, or pivot?\"\necho \"\"\necho \"Results should be written to session log.\"\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\operations\\evaluate.sh"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":31933,"output":1739,"cacheRead":12170,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45842,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774132353299}}
