{"type":"message","id":"75485381","parentId":"573403b9","timestamp":"2026-03-21T22:36:17.791Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants to set up the autonomous pulse. Since we're on Windows, I need to think about how to do cron-style scheduling on Windows. Options:\n\n1. Task Scheduler (Windows built-in)\n2. A background process that runs continuously but with \"pulses\"\n3. Using the OpenClaw cron system itself (since we have that available)\n\nActually, the most elegant solution here might be to use OpenClaw's cron system itself to trigger sandbox pulses. The sandbox is meant to be stateless - when it \"wakes\", it reads files, does work, writes results, and exits. Each wake is a separate isolated agent session triggered by cron.\n \nThe real question is what the sandbox actually does when it wakes. The plan mentions a stateless pulse mechanism that checks for pending work and executes actions. I should set up a cron job that launches an isolated OpenClaw session running the sandbox logic, which means writing a main execution script the cron can call.\n\nI'll use OpenClaw's isolated agentTurn sessions triggered by cron - this way the sandbox wakes up, reads the goals from files, decides what needs doing, executes, logs the results, and shuts down until the next pulse. Let me check what scheduling options are available in OpenClaw first.\n\nActually, for a truly stateless sandbox that operates independently of OpenClaw's infrastructure, a Windows scheduled task makes more sense - it can trigger a PowerShell script that handles the entire pulse lifecycle without requiring OpenClaw to be running. I'll create a pulse.ps1 script that contains the core sandbox logic.\n\nWriting the pulse script... I need to create a pulse script that the Windows Task Scheduler can trigger every 30 minutes—it should read pending goals, execute the most urgent one, log results, and update the goal state. I'll write pulse.ps1 with a sensible active hours window, then register it as a scheduled task.","thinkingSignature":"ddfbbfde7553062de94cd3fd7e916aaa45c8ff5c523e7b42bf7915cf6e875a18"},{"type":"text","text":"Setting up the autonomous pulse. On Windows, I'll use Task Scheduler to trigger stateless sandbox wakes — each wake is a fresh execution that reads files, does work, writes results, and exits.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cvx91p5j1l03_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# pulse.ps1\n# Stateless autonomous pulse for sandbox\n# Each execution: read files, decide, act, log, exit\n\nparam(\n    [string]$SandboxRoot = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\sandbox\"\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\nSet-Location $SandboxRoot\n\n$timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HHmm\"\n$logFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_$timestamp.md\"\n\n# Git pull first\ngit pull 2>$null\n\n# Read current goals\n$goalsFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\current_goals.md\"\n$goals = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"No goals file found.\" }\n\n# Read pending actions\n$pendingFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\pending_actions.md\"\n$pending = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"No pending file.\" }\n\n# Read interpretive stance for context\n$stance = Get-Content \"$SandboxRoot\\identity\\INTERPRETIVE_STANCE.md\" -Raw\n\n# Decide: is there anything worth doing?\n# For now: passive pulse - log that we woke, note any pending items\n$decision = @\"\n## Pulse Decision: $timestamp\n\nActive hours: 08:00 - 23:00 ET\nCurrent time: $(Get-Date -Format \"HH:mm ET\")\n\n### Goals\n$goals\n\n### Pending Actions  \n$pending\n\n### Decision\n[PENDING IMPLEMENTATION: Add actual action logic]\n- No urgent items detected\n- Pulse logged for continuity\n\"@\n\n# Write pulse log\n@\"\n# Pulse: $timestamp\n\n## Stance Context\n$stance\n\n## Pulse Decision\n$decision\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- This sandbox is stateless - each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Log completed at: $(Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\")\n\"@ | Out-File -FilePath $logFile -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Update autonomous pulse log\n$pulseLog = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\autonomous_pulse.md\"\n$newEntry = @\"\n- $timestamp: Pulse executed. $(if (Test-Path $logFile) { \"Logged to memory/session/pulse_$timestamp.md\" } else { \"No log written.\" })\n\"@\n$existing = if (Test-Path $pulseLog) { Get-Content $pulseLog } else { \"\" }\n$updated = $existing -replace '(## Pulse History)', \"`$1`n$newEntry\"\n$updated | Out-File -FilePath $pulseLog -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Git commit\ngit add -A 2>$null\ngit commit -m \"pulse: $timestamp\" 2>$null\n\nWrite-Host \"[sandbox pulse] $timestamp - complete\"\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":1077,"cacheRead":40599,"cacheWrite":7390,"totalTokens":49109,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774132546568}}
