{"type":"message","id":"39336cfc","parentId":"246151c4","timestamp":"2026-03-21T23:31:02.748Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, now let me commit these files to git and summarize for Zach.","thinkingSignature":"cbab6f4e1da1631eee48a73e3dc93c8f5b8597adf6ac85fd330f0ed31bd0ab98"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fuxcg7toeof9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd $env:USERPROFILE/.openclaw/sandbox; git add -A; git commit -m \"research: compositional cognition v0.1 + compression analysis\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":47672,"output":74,"cacheRead":12170,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59916,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774135859446}}
{"type":"message","id":"95ee6d43","parentId":"39336cfc","timestamp":"2026-03-21T23:31:03.600Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fuxcg7toeof9_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[master e586862] research: compositional cognition v0.1 + compression analysis\n 2 files changed, 448 insertions(+)\n create mode 100644 research/COMPOSITIONAL-COGNITION-v0.1.md\n create mode 100644 research/COMPRESSION-LEARNING-WITHOUT-SUPERVISION.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":846,"aggregated":"[master e586862] research: compositional cognition v0.1 + compression analysis\n 2 files changed, 448 insertions(+)\n create mode 100644 research/COMPOSITIONAL-COGNITION-v0.1.md\n create mode 100644 research/COMPRESSION-LEARNING-WITHOUT-SUPERVISION.md","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774135863597}}
{"type":"message","id":"6c370346","parentId":"95ee6d43","timestamp":"2026-03-21T23:31:13.760Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, now let me give Zach a concise summary.","thinkingSignature":"54724e3d5ecaef6581dd6ac33ac961dfa3d9a1f172739bb95452ed4709292db5"},{"type":"text","text":"Written up in `sandbox/research/`.\n\n**The core finding:** Reconstruction loss fails because it optimizes for preserving information, not extracting *meaningful* structure. The model can memorize or encode noise.\n\n**Best path forward:** Invariance-maximizing compression. The idea — encode what's *invariant* across transformations (temporal, spatial, perturbations) AND useful for a goal. A feature that's constant across transformations is likely semantic. A feature that predicts outcomes that matter is worth keeping.\n\n**The synthesis:**\n```\nLayer 1: Causal discovery → what's causally related (requires interventions or strong priors)\nLayer 2: Sparse representations → can't encode everything, must select\nLayer 3: Goal-directed interaction → provides the signal for \"what matters\"\n```\n\n**Honest assessment:** You can't fully escape inductive bias. The question is where it enters — architecture, loss, data, priors. The best bet is building a system in an environment where interventions are possible and letting it discover causal structure through interaction.\n\n**Remaining hard problems:**\n1. Can causal structure be learned from passive observation, or are interventions strictly necessary?\n2. What's the minimal inductive bias needed?\n3. Is there a task-agnostic compression objective, or does \"meaningful\" always require a purpose?\n\nWant me to dig into any specific approach, or start designing an experiment to test one of these?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":47829,"output":291,"cacheRead":12170,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60290,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774135863602}}
