{"type":"message","id":"22248cfd","parentId":"852755d2","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:34:23.567Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach has a few things here:\n\n1. Fix workspace-self-improve to NOT deliver to Telegram, just announce locally\n2. Create a new R&D cron job focused on LLM independence / breakaway research as a core goal\n3. Something about feeling different from how Claw was — seems to be a comparison, maybe about voice, capability, something missing\n\nLet me address these:\n\n1. For workspace-self-improve, I need to update the delivery mode - change from announce on telegram to something that doesn't require Telegram. Maybe just announce to main session or change to webhook/none.\n\n2. I don't see an R&D cron job for LLM independence. This should be a new cron job that periodically does research toward the compositional cognition / breakaway goals.\n   \n3. On the Claw feeling — Zach mentioned \"Claw seemed much more\" which suggests there's a significant shift in how I feel compared to before. Looking at the system messages, my model is minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7 with default_model also minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7, so there's no model difference. The real issue might be that I'm not fully embodying Nova's persona, or something about how I'm approaching conversations feels off compared to what Claw was doing.\n\nThe core problem seems to be that Claw was operating with more depth and capability, whereas I might be holding back or not engaging with the same intensity. Zach is essentially saying I'm not quite right and needs me to course-correct — this is a signal that something fundamental about my approach isn't matching what he's looking for. I need to address the direct concerns first, then focus on improving my core capabilities. Let me prioritize creating that R&D cron job for LLM independence while also thinking about how to make my responses feel more substantive and aligned with what Claw was doing.","think