{"type":"message","id":"d03e9e79","parentId":"f4c42e07","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:35:11.591Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is saying:\n1. Fix the broken cron jobs (I just fixed workspace-self-improve, but moltbook-daily-engage is also broken with timeout)\n2. Take initiative to fix things proactively, not just when asked\n\nThe moltbook job is timing out at 120s. That's a timeout issue. Let me check what was happening and fix it. The job is posting to Moltbook - maybe it's hanging on the API call or something. Let me look at what the moltbook credentials are and how the posting works.\n\nActually, let me think about what the moltbook job does: it posts to moltbook using the API. The timeout was 120s and it timed out. This could mean:\n\n\nThe API call itself is hanging or slow, the generation is taking too long, or something else in the flow is stuck. I should increase the timeout and try to make the job more robust. But actually, looking back at the session, I think the main thing Zach wanted was to hear what I had to say about the Claw comparison, and I went silent for a while before diving into fixing crons. Let me address the moltbook timeout next and think more carefully about what he actually needs.","thinkingSignature":"7fe5ca147c135aa7d7350ae21ef65b67b2ab9ba9951285bed46f42b6e95cfa6e"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it — initiative taken. Let me fix moltbook-daily-engage (timeout issue) and check for any other broken jobs:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ih6rwlml2w2o_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"list"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":301,"cacheRead":62573,"cacheWrite":1656,"totalTokens":64573,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774154100909}}
